        Official Singles Chart on 5/6/2020

        5 June 2020 - 11 June 2020

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        CHART REVIEW

        Hey, Unverification here. I'll be starting chart reviews here on this account every week.

        Before I get into the debuts, I'm glad to see ROCKSTAR back at Number 1, but glad Rain On Me is still pretty high as well. Also nice to see GOOBA falling quickly, really not a fan of that song or the person behind it.

        That out of the way, let's get started with the first new song this week, 'I Dunno'. I'm not really the biggest fan of this. The beat is pretty nice, but it gets repetitive after a while. Tion Wayne's delivery is pretty boring on this as well. The only thing that really stands out here is Stormzy's verse, which fits really well on the beat. The whole thing is just really boring. Decent 6.

        This next song is 'Sour Candy', a song that really surprised me. I went expecting really like it, seeing as the feature is from a genre that I really don't like, but I was wrong. The song is soooo catchy, and it's been stuck in my head ever since I first heard it, especially the chorus. Lady Gaga really souds nice on this track on this. The real standout here though, is the feature, BLACKPINK. They just fit so well on this beat. Speaking of the beat, it sounds really nice and compliments the artists super well. This is definitely a 10!

        Another song from the same artist, 'Alice' is up next. Lady Gaga really has a really good voice here. he production is probably the best on the album., it's just so fun. The best part is definitely auto-tuned part at 1:36, it's just so satisfying. The lyrics on this one are kind of annoying, but that doesn't really matter for a song like this in my opinion. Overall, this isn't as good as Sour Candy, but still pretty good. This gets a decent 8 from me.

        The last song to review is 30. I find this one really boring. It's just another grime song to me. Aitch's voice really annoys me, he just sounds so bored, especially here. I really like the beat here though, it's great to just listen to. I could 100% see this one growing on me though. For now, it's a 5/10.

        As for the albums, I really like Chromatica at the top, and Kygo debuting higher than I thought he would.

        Next week, I really hope Secrets and Sour Candy go higher. Also hope to see songs like This Is America and Alright get here, they really should after the tragic events recently.

        SCORES (TLDR):
        Tion Wayne, Dutchavelli and Stormzy - I Dunno (6/10)
        Lady Gaga and BLACKPINK - Sour Candy (10/10)
        Lady Gaga - Alice (8/10)
        Aitch - 30 (5/10)

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (05/06/2020 - 11/06/2020)

        Honestly, for as much as I loved last weeks chart, it was so busy that I just wanted a cooldown week for this new one & I guess that was the case? Yeah, the albums chart had a lot of exciting activity happening on it (which well get to later), but there wasnt really much in the way of major disruption on the singles chart.

        Anyway, Im not at all surprised that Rockstar reclaimed the top spot looking at its streaming numbers across multiple platforms & I certainly dont mind that either, but am I the only one who thought Rain On Me couldve easily snuck in another week at #1? Sales & particularly radio were dominant for it all week & Lady Gaga even released a new album, so Im not going to lie, I thought it would hold up a little better. Never mind, we still got to see this song make history last week & as long as this gets enough airplay across all the major pop stations to give a few weeks in the Top 10, Ill be completely happy with how its done!

        Really though, the elephant in the room at the moment is Rover by S1MBA ft DTG. Its got to the point where its consistently strong across all formats & if it can somehow deny ACR for another week or two, I get the feeling that it might go all the way to #1 later this month! Of course, thats positive news, because the song has been growing on me a lot lately.

        Glad that Breaking Me finally made the Top 10! I know a lot of regulars here arent the biggest fans of it, but I love EDM, so its kind of hard for me not to be pleased with this, haha. I wish the same would happen with Flowers now though! Secrets is finally starting to get some momentum behind it too. Oh, speaking of dance songs, even though its a much more chilled one, Im loving that huge gain for ily (i love you baby) lower down, which only cements its positions as an early summer smash! Lets get it even higher over the next few weeks!

        Moving on from that, we have I Dunno as the highest debut of the week, also landing inside the Top 10! I actually didnt hear this hear this at all until yesterday, but yeah, I mostly like what each of the three rappers are displaying here! Sure, Tion Wayne & Dutchavelli bring a lot of grittiness to the track & both of them can ride the rubbery (if overused) bass beat reasonably well, but its Stormzys verse that really sealed the deal for me. Not only does he tick all of those boxes too, but his fast-paced delivery & confidence just stands out & lets be honest, hes probably the biggest reason why this entered the chart as high as it did! My only real criticism is that the lyrics are the same bragging that you hear in almost every UK rap song rap song that charts, with the most interesting part being that Stormzys verse might be taking shots at Chip, but hey, at least everyone here shows that they can be competent MCs, particularly Stormzy. Im not sure how thisll age for me, but for now, Ill give it a light 7/10!

        Of course, the bigger story overall this week comes from Lady Gaga! Believe it or not, Chromatica was outselling the rest of the Top 20 albums combined midway through the tracking week, but to make things even better, she even landed two debuts on the singles chart.

        Starting with Sour Candy & not only am I one of the few people here who generally enjoys a lot of K-Pop, but what also helps here is that BLACKPINK are one of my favourite female groups from the genre! They tend to be able to allow all of the members to equally show off their talent & they usually have a lot of sass too, which shows in this song. I also like how they switch between English & Korean in each line, but unfortunately, Im not sure theyre the best fit for this kind of heavier & deeper production, nor am I sold on how well their part flows into Lady Gagas! Overall though, while I think there are even better tracks on Chromatica & its probably not even the best recent hit that discusses split personality (looking at you Sweet But Psycho!), this is still a lot of fun & I get the feeling its going to be on my playlist for a while. For me, this is a light 8/10!

        As for Alice, while I probably enjoy this song a little bit more than Sour Candy, that comes down a lot more to Lady Gaga herself this time round! The whole vibe of this song just feels both euphoric & nostalgic, but my favourite part is her insane power that she shows here across a wide range. Its this kind of music of hers that I knew she was capable of, but she hadnt released in years & while I really wish Sine From Above with Elton John had been able to chart instead, Ill still happily take this one! Solid 8/10.

        Lastly, weve got 30 by Aitch annoyingly debuting six spots lower than it should have given the title, haha! Seriously though, while Ive mostly come around on Aitch over these past few months, I cant say I'm going to get on board with this one. I dont deny that hes bringing a decent amount of charisma here, but what the heck is going on with that vocal mixing?! It makes him sound so much weaker than usual, which is somehow even worsened by the faint knocks, the fuzzy underlying beat drowns almost everything else out & the alarm rings that come in completely off beat. I would talk about the content, but whats the point in doing that when its the same kind of flexing we hear in almost every song from him? Yeah, I hate to say it, but coming from the same dude who brought us Rain & Buss Down in the past year, this is a massive disappointment. Solid 3/10!

        As for the albums chart, as you mightve already gathered, I love Chromatica making an insanely big debut at #1! I kind of wish Kygo debuted in the Top 5 though, but I get that it can be hard to listen to his summery party beats right now when were all stuck in lockdown.

        Looking ahead to next week, I genuinely don't know what new music could be hitting the charts! In fact, we may even see some older hits by black artists re-enter in response to the tragedy thats been happening in America these past couple of weeks.

        Thats it from me for this review. Have a good weekend & above all, stay safe! :)

        oliviasnoodles
